week 7
In today's class, we focused on the following topics:

**Introduction to PHP**: The teacher introduced the basic concepts of PHP, including its history and its role in server-side programming.

**Installation and Configuration**: We learned how to install the PHP environment on our local machines and performed basic configurations.

**Basic Syntax**: The class covered the fundamental syntax rules of PHP, including variable declaration, data types, and simple string operations.

**First PHP Script**: The teacher guided us in writing our first PHP script, which was a simple "Hello World" program.

**Overview of WordPress**: We received an introductory overview of WordPress, including its features and its application in content management systems.

**Environment Setup**: We learned how to set up a local WordPress development environment.

This class marked the beginning of our journey into the world of PHP and WordPress, laying a solid foundation for further learning.
